SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:storytime,library,baby,toddler,reading
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Chicago Public Library\\nCost: free\\nAges: 0-60 mo
 nths\\nCategory: Film & Events\\n\\nJoin us for a screening to celebrate A
 sian American heritage month with the highly acclaimed crime drama\, Bette
 r Luck Tomorrow. Justin Lin directed and co-wrote this drama about a group
  of Asian American scholars turned gangsters in affluent Orange County\, C
 al. As they delve deeper and deeper into the depths of human depravity\, t
 hey test their luck a little too much. The dark pivot the film makes takes
  it to another level\, really cementing this as a notable and original wor
 k. Better Luck Tomorro\\n\\nMore info: https://chipublib.bibliocommons.com
 /events/69975d2081b67dfe32a770ee
LOCATION:Rogers Park\, 6907 N. Clark St.\, Chicago\, IL 60626
URL:https://chipublib.bibliocommons.com/events/69975d2081b67dfe32a770ee
