 tardom during Hollywood's silent-movie era--paired with the beautiful\, je
 alous and dumb Lina Lamont (Jean Hagen). When Lockwood becomes attracted t
 o young studio singer Kathy Selden (Reynolds)\, Lamont has her fired. But 
 with the introduction of talking pictures\, audiences laugh when they hear
  Lockwood speak for th\\n\\nMore info: https://chipublib.bibliocommons.com
 /events/69975975b48451fc3c03c3f7
