DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Field Museum - Events\\nCost: Included with admissi
 on\\nAges: For children ages 2–6 and their caregivers\\nCategory: Storyt
 ime\\n\\nFamilies with children ages 2–6 are invited to a free drop-in P
 layDate to celebrate Asian American\, Native Hawaiian\, Pacific Islander H
 eritage Month (AANHPI). During this interactive cultural storytime\, a gue
 st reader from our AANHPI Project\, Field Museum Learning Resources Educat
 or—Cyrus Tang Foundation\, will read Aloha Everything by Kaylin Melia Ge
 orge\, exploring themes of Hawaiian hula\, Native ecology\, and oral tradi
 tions. Join us for a fun-filled PlayDate with stories\, songs\, and more!\
 \n\\nMore info: https://www.fieldmuseum.org/our-events/playlab-playdates/p
 laylab-playdate-asian-american-pacific-islander-heritage-month-storytime
