 er Science Action Centers! This engaging walk-in session dives into the fa
 scinating world of global and local pollinators\, focusing on the un-bee-l
 ievable ones and the role they play in keeping our ecosystems blooming. Du
 ring this interactive presentation\, you’ll get a bee-hind-the-scenes lo
 ok at real bee specimens from around the world\, learn how to identify com
 mon native species\, and uncover the sweet details of their life cycles\, 
 habitats\, and behaviors. We hope that guests will learn about how people\
 , plants\, and pollinators are all connected and that they can help pollin
 ators too. Presenters include Bruno de Medeiros\, Assistant Curator of Ins
 ects\; Aster Hasle\, Lead Conservation Ecologist and Nicole Machuca\, Envi
 ronmental Social Scientist.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.fieldmuseum.org/ou
 r-events/meet-a-scientist/bee-curious-up-close-and-un-bee-lievable
LOCATION:Field Museum\, 1400 S Lake Shore Dr\, Chicago\, IL 60605
URL:https://www.fieldmuseum.org/our-events/meet-a-scientist/bee-curious-up
 -close-and-un-bee-lievable
