DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Chicago Public Library\\nCost: free\\nAges: 0-60 mo
 nths\\nCategory: Storytime\\n\\nMenopause is a natural transition that is 
 often misunderstood\, under-discussed\, and filled with conflicting inform
 ation. This monthly series brings together experts\, advocates\, and real 
 women’s experiences to shed light on every stage of the journey. From ho
 rmones to mental health\, relationships to research\, each session offers 
 practical tools\, evidence-based insight\, and space for honest conversati
 on. Together\, we’ll replace confusion with clarity\, and empower each o
 ther to navigate menopause w\\n\\nMore info: https://chipublib.bibliocommo
 ns.com/events/697a4bfc834cbb3dea29e90f
